parser
Class Parser

java.lang.Object
  parser.Parser

public class Parser
extends java.lang.Object

Parser will evaluate a String (as a char[]) as a math expression.
Uses recursive descent parsing.

Grammar: 

  
 expr   ::= term     | expr + term     | expr - term
  
 term   ::= factor   | term * factor   | term / factor | term ^ factor
  
 factor ::= ( expr ) | number|variable | -factor


Author:
Mike Facelle

Method Detail

evaluate

public double evaluate()
                throws parser.exceptions.InvalidParseException
Begins the recursive loop of parsing and evaluating the function String, at the x value specified in this class.

Returns:
the value of the expression for the specified x value
Throws:
parser.exceptions.InvalidParseException - When any of the other exceptions in parser.exceptions are thrown.
When the other exceptions are thrown, this method performs these operations: UnbalancedParenthesesException: Adds a ')' for each missing ')' detected in the function String. InvalidWordException and InvalidNumberException: Both of these change the function String into "-x".
